<TITLE> HT Imam faces case over Islam remarks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 4 (bdnews24.com)  A criminal case has been filed against the prime minister's adviser HT Imam for hurting religious sentiment. Supreme Court lawyer Mridha Md Rashed Sarwar Palash filed the petition with the Dhaka's Chief Metropolitan Magistrate Court on Sunday following a speech given by Imam two days ago. A correspondent from the news agency Focus Bangla , the published of the newspaper Naya Diganta Shamsul Huda and its editor Alamgir Mohiuddin are also named as defendants. The initial hearing will take place later in the day, Aminul Gani Tito, lawyer for the complainant, told bdnews24.com. The case relates to comments that Imam is claimed to have made when he addressed a meeting titled 'The trial of war criminals in the eye of Islam' organised by the Awami Ulama League on Friday. In an article published the following day in the newspaper Naya Diganta  which was quoting the news agency Focus Bangla - it was stated that Imam had said that it was the Awami League which saved Islam in the country and that Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman introduced Islam to this country. In his petition to the court, the complainant claims that Imam's statement had hurt religious sentiment and defamed the preacher of Islam Hazrat Mohammad and his followers as well. Four lawyers have been made witnesses in the case. bdn
